## Protocol

Before writing any Pine Script v6 code:
1. Read LESSONS_LEARNED.md — 11 known errors
2. Use LLM_MANIFEST.md to find the correct reference file
3. Read that file, then write the code
4. On error: solve + append to LESSONS_LEARNED.md

## LESSONS_LEARNED Summary (11 Errors)

| # | Error | Fix |
|---|-------|-----|
| 1 | `ta.stoch()` not a tuple | `float k = ta.stoch(...)` |
| 2 | `math.avg()` doesn't exist | `(a + b) / 2` |
| 3 | `request.security()` tuple syntax | square brackets required |
| 4 | Wrong futures commission type | `cash_per_contract` |
| 5 | EMA cross without volume = fakeout | add volume filter |
| 6 | Repainting with request.security() | `[1]` + `lookahead_on` |
| 7 | `alertcondition()` in strategy | use `alert()` in `if` block |
| 8 | `barstate.islast` in strategy | use `barstate.isconfirmed` |
| 9 | Multi-line `and` at line start | single line or `and` at end |
| 10 | `calc_on_every_tick=true` | remove — breaks backtest |
| 11 | `barstate.islast` in strategy | use `barstate.isconfirmed` |

## v5 → v6

| ❌ v5 | ✅ v6 |
|-------|-------|
| `study()` | `indicator()` |
| `security()` | `request.security()` |
| `input(14, type=input.integer)` | `input.int(14)` |
| `array.new_float()` | `array.new<float>()` |
| `[k, d] = ta.stoch(...)` | `float k = ta.stoch(...)` |
| `math.avg(a, b)` | `(a + b) / 2` |
| `alertcondition()` in strategy | `alert()` |
| `barstate.islast` in strategy | `barstate.isconfirmed` |
| `calc_on_every_tick = true` | remove |
| Multi-line `and` at start | single line |

## VIOP Template

```pine
//@version=6
strategy("VIOP Strategy [trugurpala]",
    commission_type  = strategy.commission.cash_per_contract,
    commission_value = 2.0,
    slippage         = 2)
bool inSession = not na(time(timeframe.period, "0930-1815", "UTC+3"))
if not inSession and inSession[1]
    strategy.close_all(comment="Session end")
```

